---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Header     from '../components/astro/Header.astro';
import Footer     from '../components/astro/Footer.astro';
import Accordion  from '../components/astro/Accordion.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="Prostate Hub - Stage 0">
  <Header />
  
  <main class="my-8 container mx-auto px-4">
    <section class="text-center p-8 mb-8">
      <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-4">Stage 0: Understanding Prostate Health</h1>
      <p class="text-lg max-w-3xl mx-auto">
        Educational information designed for younger audiences to build awareness about prostate health and cancer prevention.
      </p>
    </section>
    
    <div class="flex flex-col md:flex-row gap-8">
      <div class="md:w-1/3 border border-gray-200 bg-fuchsia rounded-lg p-4">
        <h2 class="text-xl font-bold mb-4">Statistics</h2>
        <div class="space-y-4">
          <p>In New Zealand, approximately 4,334 men are diagnosed with prostate cancer annually.</p>
          <p>Around 740 men die from prostate cancer each year in New Zealand, which is more than twice the road toll.</p>
          <p>1 in 8 men will be diagnosed with prostate cancer in their lifetime.</p>
          <div class="h-32 border border-gray-200 rounded-lg flex items-center justify-center">
            [Chart Placeholder: Prostate Cancer Incidence by Age]
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

    <div class="md:w-2/3">
      <Accordion title="General Knowledge About Prostate Cancer" initiallyOpen={true}>
        <div class="space-y-4">
          <p>The prostate is a small gland in men that produces seminal fluid to nourish and transport sperm. Prostate cancer occurs when cells in the prostate begin to grow uncontrollably.</p>
          
          <p>Understanding prostate health early in life can help with early detection and prevention strategies later on.</p>
        </div>
      </Accordion>
      
      <Accordion title="Preventative Measures">
        <div class="space-y-4">
          <p>While there's no guaranteed way to prevent prostate cancer, certain lifestyle choices may help reduce your risk:</p>
          <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2">
            <li>Maintain a healthy diet rich in fruits, vegetables, and whole grains</li>
            <li>Exercise regularly</li>
            <li>Maintain a healthy weight</li>
            <li>Know your family history - men with close relatives who have had prostate cancer are at higher risk</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </Accordion>
      
      <Accordion title="When to Start Screening">
        <div class="space-y-4">
          <p>The Prostate Specific Antigen (PSA) test is a blood test that can help detect prostate cancer early.</p>
          <p>Consider talking to your doctor about prostate screening if:</p>
          <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2">
            <li>You are over 50 years old</li>
            <li>You have a family history of prostate cancer</li>
            <li>You are of African or Caribbean descent (these groups have higher risk)</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </Accordion>
      
      <Accordion title="Resources for Young Men">
        <div class="space-y-4">
          <p>Additional resources for learning about prostate health:</p>
          <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2">
            <li><a href="#" class="text-blue-600 hover:underline">New Zealand Prostate Cancer Foundation</a></li>
            <li><a href="#" class="text-blue-600 hover:underline">New Zealand Cancer Society</a></li>
            <li><a href="#" class="text-blue-600 hover:underline">Ministry of Health Guidelines</a></li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </Accordion>
    </div>
  </main>
  <Footer />
</BaseLayout>